00:36:12,544 --> 00:36:15,806
it in Unreal to try and represent those ideas.

544
00:36:16,086 --> 00:36:22,130
And we invited them back in to have a look at what we've done and then they would tell

545
00:36:22,170 --> 00:36:24,291
us, oh that feels a bit awful, that doesn't feel right.

546
00:36:24,771 --> 00:36:28,734
Obviously everyone's experience is unique but there did seem to be enough of a common

547
00:36:28,794 --> 00:36:35,198
thread amongst them that we could really refine the visual perceptual representations in the

548
00:36:35,218 --> 00:36:35,418
game.

549
00:36:37,467 --> 00:36:41,048
So yeah, it's the classic iterative process we all use in games, but instead of applying

550
00:36:41,088 --> 00:36:44,590
it to mechanics, we're applying it to people's lived experience.

551
00:36:49,832 --> 00:36:51,233
So the camera viewpoint.

552
00:36:51,673 --> 00:36:56,555
I think one thing that struck me is that our mind's eye doesn't always see in the first

553
00:36:56,595 --> 00:36:56,835
person.

554
00:36:56,855 --> 00:37:00,297
If you think about memory, sometimes you see yourself in the third person and it's quite

555
00:37:00,337 --> 00:37:01,517
easy to sit there where you are.

556
00:37:02,985 --> 00:37:05,707
and project yourself so that you're looking at the back of your head.

557
00:37:05,827 --> 00:37:08,609
And then when you remember that memory, you remember looking at the back of your head.

558
00:37:09,670 --> 00:37:12,151
It's quite a strange concept.

559
00:37:14,133 --> 00:37:19,056
And I thought the third-person camera view actually could be used to give you a feeling of disassociation,

560
00:37:19,537 --> 00:37:22,138
which for some people is a real thing, where

561
00:37:22,599 --> 00:37:25,201
they just don't feel like they live inside their own skin.

562
00:37:25,741 --> 00:37:27,402
They feel like strangers in their own skin.

563
00:37:30,534 --> 00:37:35,336
So, this would mean letting go of standard film theory and camera cuts.

564
00:37:35,376 --> 00:37:38,778
The game would be just one continuous uncomfortable shot.

565
00:37:39,598 --> 00:37:43,400
Whether it's cutscene or gameplay, it would also mean that there would be no health bars,

566
00:37:43,420 --> 00:37:48,203
no hit points, no inventory, no tutorials, nothing that would break you out of the idea

567
00:37:48,243 --> 00:37:52,645
that you're fully immersed in this world as an observer, as part of Senua's psyche, and

568
00:37:52,665 --> 00:37:53,786
a participant.

569
00:37:54,126 --> 00:37:57,208
You are her mind's eye, a watchful mind's eye.

